text.tspan: One way to subtract two vectors graphically, such as and in the
figure below, is to look at their x- and y- components in "ijk" notation:
1.) We first write each vector in ijk notation by putting the x-components in front
of the vector , and the y-components in front of the vector , and adding them
together. For example, has an x-component of 5 and a y-component of 2,
so we write . We write a similar expression for .
2.) We now subtract from by grouping the terms together and the terms.
3.) We draw our new vector with the x and y components we found from the
subtraction. So, we'll have an x-component of 4 and a y-component of -1.
